text: David John MacGibbon (born 13 May 1934) is an Australian politician. He is a member of the Liberal Party. He served as a Senator for Queensland from 1978 to 1999. MacGibbon was born in Brisbane, Queensland, and grew up in Maryborough. He married Pamela Beak in 1958. The couple had four children. ==References== Category:1934 births Category:Living people Category:Liberal Party of Australia politicians Category:Members of the Australian Senate Category:Politicians from Brisbane
